funkSbrTrapFSNormal.description: This trap will be sent when the the number of bytes available in the file system from which the server is running has risen above a specified threshold.

funkSbrTrapConcurrencyReconnect.name: funkSbrTrapConcurrencyReconnect
funkSbrTrapConcurrencyReconnect.description: This trap will be sent when Radius reconnects to the concurrency server after it has sent a ConcurrencyFailure, ConcurrentyTimeout, or ConcurrencyLocalProxyFailure trap.

funkSbrTrapSQLReconnect.name: funkSbrTrapSQLReconnect
funkSbrTrapSQLReconnect.description: This trap will be sent when Radius reconnects to the SQL database after it has sent a SQLConnectFail trap.

funkSbrTrapLDAPReconnect.name: funkSbrTrapLDAPReconnect
funkSbrTrapLDAPReconnect.description: This trap will be sent when Radius reconnects to the LDAP server after it has sent a LDAPConnectFail trap.

funkSbrTrapUserAccountLocked.name: funkSbrTrapUserAccountLocked
funkSbrTrapUserAccountLocked.description: This trap will be sent when a user's account becomes locked out due to an excessive number of rejected authentication attempts within a defined period of time.

funkSbrTrapUserAccountReleased.name: funkSbrTrapUserAccountReleased
funkSbrTrapUserAccountReleased.description: This trap will be sent when a user's account, previously locked out due to an excessive number of rejected authentication attempts, becomes unlocked.

funkSbrTrapProxySpoolReconnect.name: funkSbrTrapProxySpoolReconnect
funkSbrTrapProxySpoolReconnect.description: This trap will be sent when the proxy accounting spooler reconnects to the target realm after it has sent a ProxySpoolTimeout trap.

funkSbrTrapIPAddrPoolNormal.name: funkSbrTrapIPAddrPoolNormal
funkSbrTrapIPAddrPoolNormal.description: This trap will be sent when the number of available IP addresses in any pool has risen above a specified threshold.

funkSbrTrapCmdArgBadPrivDir.name: funkSbrTrapCmdArgBadPrivDir
funkSbrTrapCmdArgBadPrivDir.description: This trap will be sent when an invalid private directory is specified on the command line used to launch the RADIUS server. The command line option is ignored.

funkSbrTrapLowThreads.name: funkSbrTrapLowThreads
funkSbrTrapLowThreads.description: This trap will be sent when the count of threads available for the accounting or authentication server drops below a configurable threshold. An informational trap is sent when the count of available threads (at some future point) rises to an acceptable level.

funkSbrTrapConcurrencyFailure.name: funkSbrTrapConcurrencyFailure
funkSbrTrapConcurrencyFailure.description: This trap will be sent when communications with the RADIUS concurrency server fails. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapConcurrencyTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapConcurrencyTimeout
funkSbrTrapConcurrencyTimeout.description: This trap will be sent when communications with the RADIUS concurrency server times out. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapConcurrencyLocalProxyFailure.name: funkSbrTrapConcurrencyLocalProxyFailure
funkSbrTrapConcurrencyLocalProxyFailure.description: This trap will be sent when a local error prevents the RADIUS server from sending a proxy request to the RADIUS concurrency server. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapStaticAcctProxyTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapStaticAcctProxyTimeout
funkSbrTrapStaticAcctProxyTimeout.description: This trap will be sent when the RADIUS server times out in an attempt to forward an accounting request to the location specified by the static proxy option. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapStaticAcctProxyLocalFailure.name: funkSbrTrapStaticAcctProxyLocalFailure
funkSbrTrapStaticAcctProxyLocalFailure.description: This trap will be sent when the RADIUS server encounters a local failure in an attempt to forward an accounting request to the location specified by the static proxy option. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapLowFSSpace.name: funkSbrTrapLowFSSpace
funkSbrTrapLowFSSpace.description: This trap will be sent when the amount of space available in the file system in which the server's private directory resides falls below a configurable threshold. An informational trap is sent when the amount of available space (at some future point) rises to an acceptable level.

funkSbrTrapSQLConnectFail.name: funkSbrTrapSQLConnectFail
funkSbrTrapSQLConnectFail.description: This trap will be sent when the connection to a SQL database has failed. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the timeout.

funkSbrTrapSQLDisconnect.name: funkSbrTrapSQLDisconnect
funkSbrTrapSQLDisconnect.description: This trap will be sent when a disconnect to a SQL database occurs. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the disconnect.

funkSbrTrapSQLTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapSQLTimeout
funkSbrTrapSQLTimeout.description: This trap will be sent when a timeout occurs during an attempt to perform transactions to a SQL database. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the timeout.

funkSbrTrapAcctDbTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapAcctDbTimeout
funkSbrTrapAcctDbTimeout.description: This trap will be sent when the access to the accounting database has timed out. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the timeout.

funkSbrTrapAcctDbFailure.name: funkSbrTrapAcctDbFailure
funkSbrTrapAcctDbFailure.description: This trap will be sent when the access to the accounting database has failed. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapVerifyServerTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapVerifyServerTimeout
funkSbrTrapVerifyServerTimeout.description: This trap will be sent when an attempt to communicate with the Verification Server has timed out. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the timeout.

funkSbrTrapVerifyServerFail.name: funkSbrTrapVerifyServerFail
funkSbrTrapVerifyServerFail.description: This trap will be sent when an attempt to communicate with the Verification Server has failed. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapLDAPConnectFailure.name: funkSbrTrapLDAPConnectFailure
funkSbrTrapLDAPConnectFailure.description: This trap will be sent when a connect failure takes place to an LDAP server.

funkSbrTrapLDAPRequestTimeouts.name: funkSbrTrapLDAPRequestTimeouts
funkSbrTrapLDAPRequestTimeouts.description: This trap will be sent when an request sent to the LDAP Server has timed out. The trap is 'diluted', i.e. it is sent only once for every 'n' occurrences of the failure.

funkSbrTrapLDAPDisconnect.name: funkSbrTrapLDAPDisconnect
funkSbrTrapLDAPDisconnect.description: This trap will be sent when a disconnect to a LDAP server occurs.

funkSbrTrapLDAPRequestTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapLDAPRequestTimeout

funkSbrTrapProxySpoolTimeout.name: funkSbrTrapProxySpoolTimeout
